001package imagingbook.lib.tuples;
002
003/**
004 * A tuple with exactly 4 elements of arbitrary types.
005 *
006 * @param <T0> the type of element 0
007 * @param <T1> the type of element 1
008 * @param <T2> the type of element 2
009 * @param <T3> the type of element 3
010 */
011public final class Tuple4<T0, T1, T2, T3> implements Tuple {
012        
013        public final T0 item0;
014        public final T1 item1;
015        public final T2 item2;
016        public final T3 item3;
017        
018        public Tuple4(T0 item0, T1 item1, T2 item2, T3 item3) {
019                this.item0 = item0;
020                this.item1 = item1;
021                this.item2 = item2;
022                this.item3 = item3;
023        }
024        
025        @Override
026        public String toString() {
027                return String.format("<%s,%s,%s,%s>", item0.toString(), item1.toString(), item2.toString(), item3.toString());
028        }
029
030        public static <T0, T1, T2, T3> Tuple4<T0, T1, T2, T3> from(T0 val0, T1 val1, T2 val2, T3 val3) {
031                return new Tuple4<>(val0, val1, val2, val3);
032        }
033        
034}
